If `el` is a dom element you need to turn it into a jQuery object in order to use jQuery methods

Also , the proper method for targeting the previous sibling is [`prev()`][1] since `before()` is an insertion method

Try something like:

    callback_loaded: function(el) {
      var $prev = $(el).prev();
      if ($prev.hasClass(&#39;img_overlay&#39;)) {
        $prev.addClass(&#39;class_name&#39;);
      }
    },


  [1]: https://api.jquery.com/prev/

